<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="131" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,151,536]" pageId="20" pageNumber="131">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,404,429]" pageId="20" pageNumber="131">Discussion.</emphasis>
Smith (
<number box="[429,487,404,428]" pageId="20" pageNumber="131" value="1991.0">1991</number>
) established 
<taxonomicName box="[641,843,404,429]" class="Arachnida" family="Aturidae" genus="Ameribrachypoda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="20" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[641,843,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="131">Ameribrachypoda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName authority="Cook, 1963" authorityName="Cook" authorityYear="1963" box="[1060,1432,404,429]" class="Arachnida" family="Aturidae" genus="Phreatobrachypoda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="20" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1060,1283,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="131">Phreatobrachypoda</emphasis>
Cook, 
<number box="[1373,1432,404,429]" pageId="20" pageNumber="131" value="1963.0">1963</number>
</taxonomicName>
. This treatment was followed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Smith" box="[519,767,439,464]" pageId="20" pageNumber="131" refString="Smith, I. M. &amp; Cook, D. R. (1991) Water mites. Chapter 16. In: Thorp, J. &amp; Covich, A. (Eds.), Ecology and classification of North American freshwater invertebrates. Academic Press, San Diego, CA, pp. 523 - 592. [total page number 911 pp.]" type="book chapter" year="1991">
Smith &amp; Cook (
<number box="[701,759,440,464]" pageId="20" pageNumber="131" value="1991.0">1991</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Smith" box="[824,1033,439,464]" pageId="20" pageNumber="131" refString="Smith, I. M., Cook, D. R. &amp; Smith, B. P. (2001) Water mites and other arachnids. Chapter 16. In: Thorpe, J. &amp; Covich, A. (Eds.), Ecology and classification of North American freshwater invertebrates. 2 nd Edition. Academic Press, Waltham, Massachusetts, pp. 551 - 659. [1056 pp.] http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1016 / B 978 - 012690647 - 9 / 50017 - X" type="book chapter" year="2001">
Smith 
<emphasis box="[900,950,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="131">et al</emphasis>
. (2001
</bibRefCitation>
, 2010). Here we propose to elevate 
<taxonomicName box="[151,353,476,501]" class="Arachnida" family="Aturidae" genus="Ameribrachypoda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="20" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,353,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="131">Ameribrachypoda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to full generic status based on the autapomorphic broadly elliptical shape of the body, coarse texture of the idiosomal sclerites and presence of two pairs of prominent ridges on the dorsal shield.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
